# ============================================================================
# ~/.claude is symlinked here (see scripts/link-dotfiles.sh), so this directory
# IS the live Claude Code state: OAuth credentials, chat history, per-project
# session data, caches — hundreds of MB, much of it secret. We therefore IGNORE
# EVERYTHING by default and re-include only the hand-picked config worth syncing.
# To start tracking something new, add another `!name` line below.
# NOTE: git ignore patterns do NOT support trailing inline comments — keep each
# `!pattern` on its own line.
# ============================================================================

# Ignore everything at the top level...
/*

# ...except this ignore file and the curated config below.

!.gitignore

# Global instructions.
!CLAUDE.md

# MCP server list (currently empty — re-check it holds no tokens before commit).
!mcp.json

# Small helper scripts kept on PATH.
!bin/

# Hook / helper scripts.
!get-session-title.sh
!notify-needs-input.sh
!notify-stop.sh

# Tracked: the curated permissions/plugins/prefs. The secret-bearing `env`
# block (Honeycomb key, telemetry, email) lives in settings.local.json instead,
# which stays ignored below.
!settings.json

# Defense in depth — never let these slip in even if a rule above gets broad.
.credentials.json
claude.json
.claude.json
history.jsonl
settings.local.json
*.bak
*.bak.*
*.tmp.*
